gr.forth.ics.jbenchy
Interface Aggregator

All Superinterfaces:
AggregateBuilder, ReportBuilder
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractAggregator
public interface Aggregator
extends ReportBuilder

An aggregator records measurements defined by a schema, and then allows aggregated reports to be generated according to a number of variables.

Each stored record must conform to the schema of this aggregator, that is, have a value (or binding) for each variable defined in the schema with a compatible type.

Reports are generated by picking a set of variables. All distinct combinations of values for this set are taken, and each different combination groups all records having those exact variable bindings. The value of each combination is the aggregation of the grouped records, according to an Aggregate function.

For example, if there were these stored records:

COLOR SIZE VALUE
"RED" "BIG" 15.0
"RED" "SMALL" 20.0
"BLUE" "BIG" 20.0
"BLUE" "SMALL" 25.0
"YELLOW" "BIG" 23.0

A report of the average for each distinct "COLOR" (which would be requested with: averageOf("VALUE").per("COLOR"), returning a Records object) would yield these results:

COLOR null
RED 17.5
BLUE 22.5
YELLOW 23.0

The column keyed with null contains the results of the aggregations. The value for this column, for each record in the results, can also be accessed with Record.getValue() method.

The max value per distinct size (accordingly, maxOf("VALUE").per("SIZE")) would yield:

SIZE null
SMALL 25.0
BIG 23.0

Similarly, the count of all records (or simply count().perAll()), regardless of variables, would yield:

null
5

The semantics of the reports generation are strictly equivalent to SQL's GROUP BY clause.

The results can be ordered (see Order and Orders) and filtered (see Filter and Filters), by prepending the report() calls with ordered() and/or restricted() calls, in chained method calls fashion.

For example, to order colors lexicographically, and exclude "YELLOW", this would be written: 

 ordered(Orders.asc("COLOR")).filtered(Filters.notEq("COLOR", "YELLOW")).sumOf("...").per(..., "COLOR");

andreou

Method Detail

record

void record(Record record)
Stores a single record into this aggregator. The record must have a non-null, compatible to its type, value for each variable required by the schema of this aggregator.

Parameters:
record - the record to be recorded

with

Aggregator with(java.lang.Object variable,
                java.lang.Object value)
Creates an aggregator with the same schema and state as this, and additionally with a variable bound to a value. This variable/value binding will be implicitly recorded whenever a record is recorded to the created aggregator.

This can be used to create an Aggregator that simplifies recording and reporting for parts of an applications where some variable/value bindings are constant. This eliminates the need to redundantly add constant bindings to the stored records.

Reports generated by the returned aggregator have an implicit filter which returns only records that have the variable/value binding.

Parameters:
variable - the variable to fix to a specific value
value - the value that the given variable will have in records stored by the returned aggregator
Returns:
an aggregator based on this aggregator, which implicitly adds the provided binding to stored records, and only reports records that conform to this binding
